Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.44,0:00:12.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当你俯瞰地球表面\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}When you look down the Earth's surface
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.27,0:00:14.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让人无法不为自然界的力量\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}it's impossible not to be impressed
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.73,0:00:18.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,与其纯粹的宏伟壮丽\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}by the sheer grandeur,splendour and power
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.40,0:00:19.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而叹为观止\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}of the natural world.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.78,0:00:29.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们呈现了众多这样的奇迹\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's been ten years since we explored these wonders
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.03,0:00:32.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在《地球脉动》这一电视节目中\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}in the first series of Planet Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.29,0:00:37.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,时至今日  世界已大有变化\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And since then, much has changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.08,0:00:42.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们将用全新的方式展示\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}We can now show life on our planet
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.39,0:00:44.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,地球上的生命\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}in entirely new ways,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.97,0:00:50.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,带你以前所未有的近距离接触动物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}bring you closer to animals than ever before,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.81,0:00:58.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,首次揭示野生动物的精彩瞬间\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and reveal new wildlife dramas for the very first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.90,0:01:04.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而且不只这些\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But that's not all.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.49,0:01:07.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们的星球也在变化\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The planet has changed, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.28,0:01:11.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大自然从未像现在一样\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Never have those wildernesses been as fragile
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.84,0:01:14.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,脆弱而又珍贵\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and as precious as they are today.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.09,0:01:21.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,恰逢自然世界这一关键时刻\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}At this crucial time for the natural world,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.14,0:01:24.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们将再次启航  踏遍全球\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}we will journey to every corner of the globe
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.06,0:01:29.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,去探索这颗星球上最宝贵的财富\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}..to explore the greatest treasures of our living planet
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.27,0:01:41.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,去揭秘动物们为了生存  突破的种种极限\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and reveal the extreme lengths animals go to to survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.05,0:02:01.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最后  我们还将回到城市\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Finally, we will explore our cities
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.22,0:02:06.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,探寻生命是如何适应这个地球上最新兴的栖息地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}to see how life is adapting to the newest habitat on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.31,0:02:11.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里是《地球脉动》第二季\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This is Planet Earth II.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.00,0:02:32.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(7500,0)\fs130\bord0\move(890,950,950,950)\b0\fsp0.4}地         球         脉         动 {\fsp0.5}  I I
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.15,0:02:38.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs130\bord0\pos(950,950)\b0\fsp0.4}地         球         脉         动 {\fsp0.5}  I I
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.63,0:02:51.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1000,1000)\fs175\fsp0\t(,\fsp10)\bord0\b0\pos(960,1050)}岛        屿
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.40,0:02:57.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,地球上有成千上万的岛屿\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There are hundreds of thousands of islands,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.62,0:03:00.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每一座岛屿都是一个迷你世界\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}each one a world in miniature,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.37,0:03:04.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是地球的一个缩影\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}a microcosm of our living planet..
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.46,0:03:09.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些偏僻岛屿上为生存所做的努力\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The struggles to survive on these remote lands
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.62,0:03:13.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,正如地球上所有生命都要面临的挑战\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}reflect the challenges faced by all life on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.40,0:03:19.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs60\fsp5\fad(1000,1000)\pos(960,1100)\bord0\b0}画 外 音\N{\fs90}大卫 · 爱登堡   爵士
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.23,0:03:29.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,巴拿马海岸线边的埃斯库多岛\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The tiny island of Escudo off the coast of Panama.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.78,0:03:35.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是侏三趾树懒的栖息地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Home to the pygmy three-toed sloth.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.62,0:03:43.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是一只雄性树懒  在这里生活得十分惬意\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This is a male, and life here suits him well.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.76,0:03:51.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,红树林为他提供食物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Mangroves provide all the leaves he can eat
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.14,0:03:53.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也没有天敌前来叨扰\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and there are no predators to worry him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.85,0:03:58.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,岛上的生活似牧歌般悠闲\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Island life may seem idyllic
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.81,0:04:01.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但这是有代价的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but it comes at a price.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.77,0:04:06.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这座岛上只有几百只雌性侏三指树懒\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There are only a few hundred pygmy sloths in existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.02,0:04:10.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而他需要配偶\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And he needs a mate.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.11,0:04:17.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这雌性的叫声\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}That's an enticing call...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.42,0:04:20.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好生诱人\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}..from a female.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.46,0:04:25.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就在不远的某个地方\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Somewhere out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.84,0:04:33.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对树懒来说  这反应堪称迅猛\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And this, for a sloth, is a quick reaction.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.04,0:05:01.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但问题是  中间隔着一渊深潭\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The problem is, there's deep water between them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.71,0:05:06.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那么一只气血方刚的树懒会怎么做呢\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}So what should any red-blooded sloth do?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.59,0:05:13.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当然是游过去\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Swim, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.13,0:05:46.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那会是她吗\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Could this be her?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.23,0:05:57.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他尽全力加快速度\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}He does his best to put on a turn of speed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.82,0:06:10.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但叫的不是她\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But she's not the one.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.03,0:06:12.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这只母树懒已经有了一只幼崽\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}She already has a baby
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.99,0:06:16.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在幼崽六个月后长大离开之前\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and she won't mate again until it leaves her
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.16,0:06:17.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她不会再次交配\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}in about six months' time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.51,0:06:30.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,即使生活在天堂之岛也会有限制\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Even life on a paradise island can have its limitations.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.15,0:06:39.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但至少她就在不远处\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But at least she can't be far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.40,0:06:47.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,地球上所有的侏三指树懒都生活在\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The world's entire population of pygmy sloths is isolated
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.95,0:06:53.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这片不及纽约中央公园大小的岛屿上\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}on a speck of land no bigger than New York's Central Park.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.84,0:07:00.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,岛屿的大小极大地影响着\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The size of an island has a huge influence
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.22,0:07:03.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,生活在那里的动物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}on the fate of those cast away there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.39,0:07:12.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是印度尼西亚的科莫多岛\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The island of Komodo in Indonesia.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.33,0:07:25.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,龙之巢穴\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Home to dragons.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.72,0:07:48.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,体长三米  重达六十八公斤\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Ten feet long and weighing an impressive 150 lbs,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.93,0:07:53.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们是地球上现存体型最大的蜥蜴\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}these are the largest living lizards on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.62,0:08:09.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大型食肉动物在岛屿上并不常见\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's unusual to find large predators on islands.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.92,0:08:17.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然而  四百万年来  科莫多巨蜥一直称霸这里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Yet, for four million years, the Komodo dragon has dominated here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.44,0:08:30.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这么小的岛屿似乎不可能\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It might seem there wouldn't be enough food
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.61,0:08:34.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为这种庞然大物提供充足的食物来源\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}to support such giants on this relatively small island.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.74,0:08:39.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但冷血爬行动物只需要\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But reptiles, being cold-blooded,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.41,0:08:43.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,肉食性哺乳动物十分之一的食物量\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}need only about a tenth of the food a carnivorous mammal would.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.33,0:08:52.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,巨蜥一餐可以支撑一个月\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A single meal will last a dragon a month.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.34,0:08:59.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们的生存之道如此成功  以至于唯一的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They're so successful, that their only serious competition
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.27,0:09:01.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,天敌就是他们的同类\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}comes from others of their own kind,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.89,0:09:05.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而这座岛上有约两千只巨蜥\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And there are some 2,000 of them here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.22,0:09:33.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然而这只巨蜥  并不是在寻找食物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This giant however, isn't looking for food.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.76,0:09:35.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他在寻找配偶\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}he's looking for a mate.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.97,0:09:43.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雌性巨蜥一年发一次情\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Female dragons come into season only once a year.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.53,0:09:55.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这一只并不排斥\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}She's receptive.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.50,0:10:06.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,目前为止  一切顺利\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}So far, so good.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.26,0:10:14.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但他误入别人的领地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But he's strayed into someone else's patch.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.14,0:10:24.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,另一只雄性巨蜥认为它才是这里的王\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Another huge male thinks he is the king here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.70,0:10:34.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,岛屿上空间有限  巨蜥的地盘时常重叠\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Space being limited on islands, dragon territories overlap,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.54,0:10:37.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,导致冲突不断\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and that creates continual conflict.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.75,0:10:49.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在巨蜥族群里  体型决定一切\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In dragon society, size is everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.07,0:11:10.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但如果双方体型相当  鹿死谁手就难以预料\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But if rivals are closely matched, the outcome can be uncertain.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.58,0:11:21.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,强壮的尾巴一击如同重锤\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Muscular tails strike with the power of sledgehammers.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.68,0:11:35.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,锯齿形状的牙齿像牛排刀一样锋利\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And their serrated teeth are as sharp as steak knives.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.95,0:11:50.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们都想要掀翻对手\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Each tries to topple his opponent.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.14,0:12:14.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,胜者出现\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Defeated.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.31,0:12:19.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只有最强壮的巨蜥  才有权交配\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Only the most powerful dragons win the right to mate.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.07,0:12:32.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,岛屿上有限的食物和空间\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The limited food and space on small islands
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.71,0:12:35.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,时常激起激烈的竞争\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}can often lead to intense competition.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.05,0:12:39.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但有些岛屿却幅员辽阔\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But some islands are immense.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.05,0:12:43.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,更像是一块小型大陆\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}More like miniature continents.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.55,0:12:49.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这为不同生命的进化与试验  提供了机会\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And these provide opportunities for life to experiment and evolve.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.89,0:12:58.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,马达加斯加是地球上最大的岛屿之一\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Madagascar is one of the biggest islands
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.23,0:13:00.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也是最古老的岛屿之一\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and also one of the oldest,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.61,0:13:05.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它在一亿两千万年前就已经脱离非洲大陆\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}having split away from Africa over 120 million years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.09,0:13:20.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,随着时间流逝与地理隔断的出现 岛上的动物们不断适应\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}With time and isolation, its animals have adapted
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.55,0:13:23.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,充分利用一切可用资源\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}to take advantage of every available niche.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.56,0:13:36.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这座岛上现存约二十五万不同的物种\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The island now has some 250,000 different species,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.15,0:13:38.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大部分都是该地区特有种\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}most found nowhere else on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.58,0:13:54.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些不是猴子  而是狐猴\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These are not monkeys, but lemurs.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.05,0:14:05.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们从同一个祖先  进化出一百个不同的种\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}From a single ancestor, about a hundred different types have evolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.65,0:14:15.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,体型最大的马达加斯加大狐猴极少下树\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The largest, the indri, seldom comes down from the branches.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.41,0:14:27.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,体型小许多的环尾狐猴  成群结队地扫荡森林地面\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The much smaller ring-tails wander in troops across the forest floor
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.12,0:14:28.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,寻找水果\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}searching for fruit.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.08,0:14:34.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,极小的驯狐猴只吃竹子\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And tiny bamboo lemurs eat nothing except bamboo.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.64,0:14:44.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为竞争者极少\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}With few competitors,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.35,0:14:49.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,狐猴能够在整片岛屿上生活\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}lemurs have been free to colonise almost every environment on the island,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.07,0:14:54.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,甚至是环境极其恶劣的地方\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Even the most extreme.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.49,0:15:06.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这只幼小的冕狐猴成长之路十分艰辛\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This baby sifaka has a hard life ahead of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.88,0:15:15.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他出生在马达加斯加广阔土地上\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}He's been born in the most arid and hostile corner
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.18,0:15:17.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最贫瘠干旱的地方\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}of Madagascar's vast landscape.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.64,0:15:24.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他还需要学习很多东西  才能在这存活下去\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}If he is to survive here, he has much to learn.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.82,0:15:34.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,刺森林的环境类似沙漠\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The spiny forest is like a desert.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.78,0:15:40.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,由于很少下雨  水和食物都很难获取\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It rarely rains, so water and food is very hard to find.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.34,0:15:52.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在树间跳跃穿梭十分危险\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Moving from tree to tree is a perilous business.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.76,0:15:58.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里几乎所有的植物表面都布满尖刺\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Here, nearly all the plants are covered with ferocious spines.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.22,0:16:04.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,幼崽的妈妈在树顶寻找鲜嫩的叶子\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}His mother searches the tree tops for the youngest leaves.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.14,0:16:11.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,嫩叶提供了这个家庭唯一的食物和水\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They provide the only food and water to sustain the family.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.75,0:16:21.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小狐猴三个月大时便开始探索世界\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}At three months old, the youngster is starting to explore.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.75,0:16:31.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很快他将不得不自己上树寻找食物了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}All too soon he will have to fend for himself up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.34,0:16:41.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但总归还是待在妈妈的背上最轻松\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But it's altogether easier to stay on mother's back.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.95,0:16:54.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果他能掌握这片森林中特有的生存方法\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}If he can master the strange ways of this forest
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.24,0:16:57.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就能在马达加斯加岛上谋得一席之地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}he will have a little corner of Madagascar to himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.33,0:17:08.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,岛屿生态迫使动物另辟蹊径\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Island life encourages animals to do things differently.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.59,0:17:12.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在某些岛上  这是必备的生存技能\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And on some islands that is essential.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.20,0:17:30.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,由于火山运动\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There are islands still forming today
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.61,0:17:33.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在仍有岛屿不断形成\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}built by volcanoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.49,0:17:39.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有些火山喷发剧烈\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Some erupt explosively.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.64,0:17:49.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有些则熔化岩石\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Others pour out rivers of molten rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.93,0:17:51.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,化作岩浆\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Lava.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.48,0:18:00.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在近五十年内\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In the last 50 years,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.15,0:18:03.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,已经形成了十个新的火山岛\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}ten new volcanic islands have been formed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.56,0:18:36.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,由于形成时间晚又常十分偏远  鲜有生命踏足\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Newly created and often remote, they're hard for colonists to reach.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.73,0:18:45.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,即使有  环境也极其难以生存\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Even those that do find these are tough places to survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.08,0:18:53.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是费尔南迪纳岛\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This is Fernandina,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.37,0:18:55.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,太平洋加拉帕戈斯群岛的一部分\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}one of the Galapagos Islands in the Pacific.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.42,0:19:03.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这座年轻的活火山岛屿一片荒凉\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Young and still volcanically active, it's a desolate place.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.07,0:19:22.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然而环岛的海中却孕育着丰富的生命\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The surrounding sea, however, is particularly rich with life.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.83,0:19:30.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而这两个不同世界的交界处\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And the frontier between these two very different worlds
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.62,0:19:34.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,生活着最奇异的爬行动物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}is the home of one of the strangest of reptiles.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.00,0:19:40.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,海鬣蜥\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Seagoing iguanas.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.88,0:19:45.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们是素食者\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They are vegetarians,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.85,0:19:48.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但由于岛上没有能吃的食物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but since there's little food for them on the land,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.52,0:19:51.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以海鬣蜥以海底的植物为食\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}marine iguanas graze on the sea floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.07,0:19:59.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这种体型的雄性海鬣蜥可潜到水下三十米\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A big male like this one can dive to 30 metres
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.57,0:20:01.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,屏住呼吸长达半小时\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and hold his breath for half an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.94,0:20:33.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,仅在费尔南迪纳岛上  就有超过七千只海鬣蜥\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There are more than 7,000 individuals on Fernandina alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.28,0:20:45.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们往返近海获取食物养活自己\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And by bringing nutrients from the sea to the land,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.37,0:20:48.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,同时还帮助了其它动物在此生存\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the iguanas help other animals to survive here, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.92,0:20:56.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,红石蟹以海鬣蜥背上的死皮为食\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Crabs feed on dead skin on the iguana's back
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.43,0:21:00.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,反过来也热情地为它们提供去角质服务\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and, in turn, provide a welcome exfoliation service.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.94,0:21:12.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小型蜥蜴还捕食纠缠海鬣蜥的苍蝇\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}While smaller lizards prey on the flies that pester the colony.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.22,0:21:40.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但岛上的生存关系并不是都如此和谐\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But not all the relationships on this island are so harmonious.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.77,0:21:50.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,海鬣蜥将蛋下在沙子里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Marine iguanas lay their eggs in sand.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.20,0:21:57.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每到六月  刚破壳的小鬣蜥异常脆弱\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In June, when the hatchlings emerge, they are vulnerable.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.58,0:22:05.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们必须到海边与成年海鬣蜥汇合\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They must join the adults at the edge of the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.13,0:22:07.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但这将是一次危险的旅程\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But the journey will be a dangerous one.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.91,0:22:35.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,游蛇\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Racer snakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.36,0:23:08.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,游蛇错失了这次机会\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The snakes miss their chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.20,0:23:19.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但还有更多的小鬣蜥将孵化而出\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But more babies are hatching.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.22,0:23:29.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些游蛇正虎视眈眈\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And now the snakes are on the alert.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.26,0:23:33.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是它们一年里最佳的捕食时机\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This is the best feeding opportunity they will get all year.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.99,0:23:54.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小鬣蜥在平地上跑得比游蛇快\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}On flat ground, a baby iguana can outrun a racer snake.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.46,0:23:58.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但周围还有其他蛇在埋伏\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But others are waiting in ambush.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.70,0:24:32.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,另一只刚孵化的小鬣蜥  第一次见识了这个危险的世界\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Another hatchling has its first glimpse of a dangerous world.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.69,0:25:37.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,蛇的视力并不是很好  但它们可以感知到移动物体\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A snake's eyes aren't very good, but they can detect movement.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.03,0:25:44.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以如果这只小鬣蜥能保持冷静 也许能逃出它们的视线\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}So if the hatch ling keeps its nerve, it may just avoid detection.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.43,0:27:22.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,近乎奇迹地逃出生天\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A near miraculous escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.89,0:27:34.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有幸活下来的小鬣蜥可以开始学习\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The lucky survivors can begin learning the unique way of life
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.32,0:27:36.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,应对这座危险岛屿的独特方式了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}demanded by this hostile island.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.75,0:27:49.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,尽管海鬣蜥是游泳的行家\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Although marine iguanas are expert swimmers,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.50,0:27:51.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们也无法横渡广阔的大海\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}they can't cross open oceans.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.76,0:28:05.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但再汹涌的海水都无法阻挡鸟类\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But even the stormiest waters are no barrier for birds.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.49,0:28:18.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,阵阵烈风加之低温\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Gale force winds and cold temperatures
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.66,0:28:21.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让新西兰亚南极地区的这座岛屿\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}make the subantarctic islands off New Zealand
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.04,0:28:25.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在冬天变得尤其不友好\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}particularly unwelcoming in winter.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.18,0:28:44.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但当短暂的夏日来临时  这里将变得风和日丽\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But when the brief summer comes, temperatures rise and winds slacken.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.04,0:29:03.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,正是游客到访的好时节\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's now that visitors arrive.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.26,0:29:10.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都趁着冬天来临之前来这里繁殖\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}All here to breed before winter returns.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.64,0:29:14.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些是斯岛黄眉企鹅\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There's the Snares penguins.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.31,0:29:25.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,海鸥也来到这里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Shearwaters come, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.32,0:29:32.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为没有天敌能够靠近这里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This is an excellent place for them to dig their nesting burrows,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.36,0:29:35.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里成为海鸥挖掘地窝的绝佳场所\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}for no predators have managed to get here.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.38,0:29:44.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很快岛上会到处都是鸟\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Soon the island is crowded with birds.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.55,0:29:50.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每只鸟都急切地想充分利用  他们短暂的繁育季节\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Every one of them eager to make the most of the short breeding season.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.93,0:29:57.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但并不是所有鸟都有伴侣\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But not everyone has a partner.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.36,0:30:08.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一只雄性新西兰信天翁正等待另一半的到来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A male Buller's albatross waits for his mate.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.20,0:30:16.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每年他们都将分开六个月  各自在海上飞行\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Each year they spend six months apart, travelling the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.25,0:30:24.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们将在这里汇合生育下一代\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They reunite here to breed.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.05,0:30:29.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但今年  雌性信天翁还没有到\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But this year, she's late.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.26,0:30:35.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不  那不是她\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}No, that's not her.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.90,0:30:42.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其他鸟儿来来往往\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The other birds come and go.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.66,0:30:54.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,时间所剩无几\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The clock is ticking.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.79,0:31:00.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果雌性信天翁还不出现 他们将错过顺利繁衍后代的机会\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}If she doesn't appear soon, it will be too late for them to breed successfully.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.67,0:31:08.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每天清晨海鸥飞离这里  为他们的孩子寻找食物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Every morning the shearwaters fly off to collect food for their young.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.74,0:31:29.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每只鸟儿似乎都在抓紧干\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Everybody else seems to be getting on with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.97,0:31:47.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,海鸥的归来意味着又一天过去了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The shearwaters' return marks another lost day.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.81,0:31:52.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这个岛上有三百万只鸟\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There are three million birds on the island,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.90,0:31:55.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但他只在乎那一只\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but only one matters to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.70,0:32:04.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这会是她吗\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Could this be her?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.38,0:32:12.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,总算回来啦\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}At last.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.72,0:32:30.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一开始雄性信天翁还有些害羞\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}At first, he's a little coy.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.00,0:32:46.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但很快就放开了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But not for long.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.05,0:32:56.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们用多年来练成的独特舞蹈\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They greet each other with the special dance
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.80,0:32:59.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,向彼此表示问候\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}they've perfected over many years.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.24,0:33:17.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果他们还打算在冬天来临前养育孩子 要做的事情还有很多\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There is much to do, if they're to raise a chick before winter returns.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.87,0:33:24.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但当你和某人分开大半年\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But when you have been apart for six months,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.79,0:33:27.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有些事需要慢慢来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}some things can't be rushed.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.69,0:33:53.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,地处温暖热带海域的岛屿  无法体验极端的季节变化\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Islands in warm tropical waters don't experience seasonal extremes.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.24,0:33:59.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,位于非洲东海岸的塞舌尔群岛\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The Seychelles, lying off the coast of East Africa,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.58,0:34:02.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是海鸟们全年的庇护天堂\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}provide a sanctuary for sea birds all the year round.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.10,0:34:22.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,塞舌尔白燕鸥是这里的永久居民\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Fairy Terns are permanent residents.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.35,0:34:29.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们筑巢并不讲究\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They take a fairly relaxed view about what constitutes a nest.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.11,0:34:33.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一根光秃秃的树枝就足够了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A bare branch is quite enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.62,0:34:47.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不过爬上去孵蛋需要格外小心\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Climbing onto it to incubate has to be done with care.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.43,0:34:59.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每年白燕鸥都会来一次\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Once a year, the noddies arrive.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.85,0:35:04.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们老实筑窝  腺果藤树能让\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They do make nests, and Pisonia trees
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.10,0:35:08.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小鸟的幼年过得安全一些\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}provide their young with a rather less precarious start in life.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.54,0:35:18.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在这个岛上筑巢看起来几乎完美\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Nesting on this island looks idyllic.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.67,0:35:24.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但美丽的表象后也有危险的一面\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But behind the beauty, there's a sinister side.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.51,0:35:33.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,塞舌尔福迪雀偷袭了无人照看的蛋\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The Seychelles fody makes quick work of an unattended egg.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.53,0:35:51.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她知道事情有点不太对劲\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}She knows something's not quite right,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.58,0:35:55.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但她孵化的意愿很强烈\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but her drive to incubate is strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.34,0:36:12.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,黑燕鸥也遇上了麻烦\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The noddies too have a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.73,0:36:18.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,随着雏鸟一天天长大\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As their chicks grow,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.69,0:36:22.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,腺果藤树长出了黏黏的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}so the pisonia trees develop seeds that are sticky
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.95,0:36:24.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,带有倒钩的种子\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and equipped with hooks.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.28,0:36:32.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,新一代黑燕鸥离巢的时候\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}By the time the young noddies leave,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.62,0:36:36.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,会带着这些搭顺风车的种子前往其它岛屿\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}they carry these hitchhiking seeds away to other islands.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.71,0:36:48.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但有时腺果藤树的策略过于成功\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But sometimes the pisonia trees are too successful.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.94,0:36:57.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果幼鸟在学习飞翔时跌落地面\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}If a fledgling, testing out its wings, drops to the ground,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.98,0:37:00.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它身上会挂满这些种子\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}it can get covered with the seeds.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.53,0:37:11.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,汁液粘腻  越粘越重\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Entangled and weighed down,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.58,0:37:16.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果它摆脱不了  就会饿死\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}if it can't free itself,the youngster will starve.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.39,0:37:35.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这样腺果藤的种子无法传播\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The Pisonia may have failed to disperse these seeds,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.94,0:37:40.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但种子扎根很快就有好肥料了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but it will soon have fertiliser for its roots.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.57,0:37:52.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这也是人们称腺果藤树为“捕鸟树”的原因\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This is why some people call the pisonia the "Bird catcher tree".
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.12,0:38:30.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,白燕鸥又下了一颗蛋\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The fairy tern laid another egg,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.29,0:38:33.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在她要养一只小鸟了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and now she has a tiny chick to feed.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.26,0:38:41.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这只小鸟很幸运\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This chick is lucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.72,0:38:48.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,等它羽翼丰满之时  腺果藤树种子已经传播完毕\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}By the time it fledges, the Pisonia seeds will have dispersed
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.93,0:38:51.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们带来的危险也将不复存在\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and the danger they brought will be gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.12,0:39:06.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再诗情画意的岛屿\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Even the most idyllic looking of islands
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.46,0:39:10.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,岛上的动物也要面临挑战\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}presents challenges for the animals living there.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.38,0:39:14.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但它们眼前的最大威胁已经改变\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But the greatest threat they face is change.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.61,0:39:34.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是印度洋上的圣诞岛\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Christmas Island in the Indian Ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.95,0:39:41.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,数百万年以来  这块遥远的陆地一直被蟹类统治着\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}For millions of years this remote spec of land has been ruled by crabs.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.33,0:39:51.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们的祖先来自海洋\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Their ancestors came from the sea,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.50,0:39:55.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但绝大多数品种现在已经适应了陆地上的生活\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but most have now adopted a land-based existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.23,0:40:09.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,鉴于它们的数量众多  彼此之间还算相对和谐\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Given there are so many of them, they get along relatively harmoniously.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.40,0:40:18.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们是这个小小蟹类乌托邦的园丁和守卫\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They're the gardeners and caretakers of a tiny crab utopia.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.28,0:40:26.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每年它们都会回到海洋中进行繁殖\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Once a year, they must all return to the sea to breed,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.17,0:40:28.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而红蟹大迁徙\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and the march of the red crabs
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.55,0:40:32.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是地球是最伟大的自然奇观之一\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}is one of the greatest natural spectacles on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.60,0:40:47.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,迁徙的红蟹数量多达五千万只\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There are 50 million of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.19,0:40:58.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这一景象让这座岛屿举世闻名\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's an event that has brought the island worldwide fame.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.92,0:41:11.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但近些年来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But in recent years,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.76,0:41:15.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,数以百万的红蟹未能成功抵达海洋\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}millions of red crabs haven't managed to reach the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.14,0:41:25.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一种入侵物种占领了这座岛屿\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}An invader has occupied this island.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.41,0:41:30.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,黄疯蚁\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Yellow crazy ants.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.74,0:41:35.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们搭乘来访的船只来到岛上  由于缺乏天敌控制\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They escape from visiting ships, and with no predators
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.16,0:41:37.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们在森林里建立了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}to control them, they have now created vast
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.00,0:41:40.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,巨大的超级蚁群\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}super colonies in the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.67,0:41:49.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当迁徙的红蟹经过它们的领地时\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}When migrating red crabs march into their territory,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.92,0:41:51.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,黄疯蚁便展开攻击\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the ants attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.22,0:41:57.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们朝红蟹的双眼和嘴中喷射酸液\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Squirting acid into the crabs' eyes and mouths.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.45,0:42:09.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,红蟹毫无还手之力\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The crabs have no defence.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.74,0:42:18.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,双目失明  迷失方向  它们便死定了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Blinded and confused, they're doomed.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.81,0:42:33.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是人类把这些蚂蚁入侵者带上了岛\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Humans brought these ant invaders here,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.44,0:42:36.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而现在人类不得不采取措施控制局面\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and now humans are having to control them.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.11,0:42:45.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,与世隔绝的动物群落 可能在数百万年内演化出了相对稳定的生态\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Isolated communities may evolve for millions of years in relative peace,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.45,0:42:51.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但当新挑战来袭  它们只能尽力去应对\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But, when new challenges arrive, they can struggle to cope.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.49,0:42:59.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,近年来濒于灭绝的物种之中\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Of all the species that have become extinct in recent years,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.30,0:43:02.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大约百分之八十是岛屿物种\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}around 80% have been islanders.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.60,0:43:11.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,人类对地球所造成的影响  比以往任何时候都要深远\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Our impact on the Earth is greater today than ever before.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.68,0:43:15.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然而有些岛屿是如此偏远\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Yet some islands are so remote
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.19,0:43:18.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以至于几乎没有人类踏足\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}that few humans have even set foot on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.82,0:43:24.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,扎沃多夫斯基岛就是一例\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Zavodovski Island is one.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.41,0:43:31.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它地处南太平洋\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It lies in the great Southern Ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.38,0:43:34.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不仅被最猛烈的海洋风暴所环绕\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's not only surrounded by the stormiest of seas,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.88,0:43:37.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而且本身就是座活火山\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}it is itself an active volcano.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.59,0:43:44.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里是地球上你最不愿居住的地方\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's the last place on Earth you would choose to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.60,0:43:56.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,除非你是一只南极帽带企鹅\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Unless you're a chinstrap penguin.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.31,0:44:02.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里的水域食物充足  但若想享用美食\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There is plenty of food in these waters, but to exploit it,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.87,0:44:05.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些企鹅得冒着生命危险\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the penguins have to risk their lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.38,0:45:00.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里的生活险象环生\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Life here is dangerous in the extreme.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.11,0:45:21.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但生活在火山上还是有一些好处的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But there are some benefits from living on a volcano.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.37,0:45:27.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,火山的热量每年早早地融化了积雪\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Its warmth melts the snow early in the year.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.79,0:45:32.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到了一月  南极地区的仲夏时节\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And, by January, the Antarctic's mid-summer,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.37,0:45:34.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,整座岛被小企鹅覆盖\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the island is covered in chicks.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.43,0:45:42.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,双亲轮流守护幼崽\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Parents take turns at guarding them
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.73,0:45:45.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,直到它们成长到足以独立生活\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}until they're large enough to be left alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.19,0:45:55.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这几只小鸟饿了  但母亲没有食物可以喂它们\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This mother's chicks are hungry, but she has no food left to give them.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.32,0:46:01.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,生存与否取决于它们的父亲  能否带着食物归来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Their survival depends on their father returning with their next meal.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.17,0:46:07.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有些企鹅确实一去不返\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But some don't make it.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.68,0:46:26.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,贼鸥不断侵扰着企鹅种群  希望能趁机叼走一只雏鸟\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Skuas harass the colony hoping to snatch a chick.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.98,0:46:36.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,母亲不能冒险离开自己的雏鸟\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}She can't risk leaving them.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.00,0:46:46.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只要父亲尽快回来  情况就会好转\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Everything will be fine, as long as their father comes back soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.70,0:47:20.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他前往远离海岸八十公里的海域捕鱼\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}He's been fishing 50 miles offshore,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.08,0:47:22.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但他现在离家不远了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but now he's not far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.00,0:47:28.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对于他和这里所有的企鹅父母来说\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}For him, however, and for all the other parents here,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.63,0:47:31.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,归途中最糟糕的一段还在后面\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the worst of the journey is still to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.63,0:48:09.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他的小脚爪帮助他攀附住陡峭的火山岩\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Tiny claws help him to get whatever grip he can on the rough lava.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.25,0:48:41.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对于这些往返的企鹅来说  现在是高峰时刻\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}For these commuters, it's rush hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.97,0:48:45.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有些企鹅今天不太顺利\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Some have had a really bad day.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.26,0:48:54.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这位父亲要走三公里的路才能到家\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The father now has a two-mile walk to the nest,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.64,0:48:57.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,肚里塞满食物  路越发难走\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and a stomach loaded with food doesn't help.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.65,0:49:08.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,周围还有全球数量最庞大的企鹅种群\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This is the largest penguin colony in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.79,0:49:19.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但由于他每隔一天就要走一遍\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But as he makes the same journey every other day,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.38,0:49:22.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,闭着眼睛都能找到回巢的路\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}he should be able to do it with his eyes closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.43,0:49:34.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,巨大的种群数量确实能保证安全\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's true that there can be safety in numbers,,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.77,0:49:37.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但当你试图寻找自己的巢穴之时\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but numbers can also be something of a problem
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.56,0:49:39.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这也会成为问题\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}when you're trying to find your own nest.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.66,0:49:48.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,母亲依然在等待\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The mother is still waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.83,0:49:53.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小鸟们快要绝望了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Her chicks are now desperate.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.09,0:50:01.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在这震耳欲聋的叫声之中\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In the midst of all this deafening chorus,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.88,0:50:04.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他可以辨识出对方特有的声音\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}he can recognise her particular cry.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.91,0:50:26.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,总算回来了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}At last.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.21,0:50:44.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,两只雏鸟都能饱餐一顿\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Both chicks will get a meal.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.94,0:50:56.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,点头示意之后  他们的母亲出发了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}With a head bob of acknowledgement, their mother now leaves.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.86,0:51:00.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,轮到她外出捕食了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's her turn to do the feeding run.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.87,0:51:13.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这种艰难的往返  是这些企鹅为了庇护所付出的代价\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This formidable commute is the price these penguins pay for sanctuary.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.93,0:51:23.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也许在我们看来  这样的天堂很奇怪\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A strange vision of paradise to us, perhaps,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.60,0:51:27.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是对于一百五十万只企鹅来说\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but, for one and a half million penguins,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.23,0:51:29.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这座岛屿满足了全部所需\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}this island has it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.66,0:51:44.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,岛屿可能既偏远而又微不足道\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Islands may seem remote and insignificant,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.84,0:51:49.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但它们仍是地球上某些珍贵动物的家园\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but they are home to some of the most precious wildlife on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.49,0:52:05.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,下一集\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Next time,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.83,0:52:08.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们会到地球的高山\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}we ascend into the planet's high mountains
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.00,0:52:14.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,发现一个壮观但充满敌意的世界\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}to discover a spectacular but hostile word.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.55,0:52:17.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,生活在那儿必须足智多谋\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}where life must be at its most resourceful,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.02,0:52:21.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只有生命力最顽强的动物可以忍受\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and only the toughest animals can endure.

